<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1625,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This species was described based on a single female specimen collected by the American limnologist and Amazon traveler Harriet Bell Merrill (
<date box="[728,863,1662,1689]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1863" valueMax="1915">1863–1915</date>
) during a research trip to South America. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[356,545,1700,1726]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref21749" refString="Rathbun R. 1911. Report on the Progress and Condition of the U. S. National Museum for the Year ending June 30, 1910. Government Printing Office, Washington." type="book" year="1911">Rathbun (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, she sold to the 
<collectionCode box="[747,837,1700,1726]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
<specimenCount box="[847,1023,1699,1726]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic">500 specimens</specimenCount>
of insects collected during her expedition to 
<collectingCountry box="[354,429,1737,1763]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, including probably the exemplar studied by Cockerell. The 
<typeStatus box="[1155,1258,1737,1763]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[1275,1361,1737,1763]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,763,789]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,720]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,265,720]" captionText="Fig. 11. Centris merrillae Cockerell, 1919, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534204). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722972/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) is housed at 
<collectionCode box="[308,398,1774,1800]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the following data label: Manaos 
<collectingCountry box="[896,968,1774,1800]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
[printed]\ Miss HBMerrill Collector [printed] 
